subSubSection.paragraph:
Female (
Figs. 80–82
). Integument mostly dark-brown; antennomeres reddish-brown, lighter toward apex. Head, excluding mandibles, about as long as prothorax at middle. Sculpture on dorsal surface of head and area behind eyes similar to that in male, but punctures inside of sulcus finer. Distance between upper eye lobes about equal to length of scape; distance between lower eye lobes slightly larger than length of scape. Frons and vertex almost glabrous. Submentum similar as in male. Antennae with 13 segments, slightly surpassing basal one-third of elytra. Scape more slender than in male, not reaching posterior ocular edge. Antennomere III 0.9 times as long as scape; antennomeres III–XII without distinct imbrication, distinctly projected after VI at outer distal edge. Prothorax as in male, except glabrous. Metasternum glabrous, slightly longer than ventrite I. Ventrites almost glabrous.
